{
  "title": "ISic003035. Text engraved on wall of a rock-cut tomb",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: <a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/UQRFDXEG\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/UQRFDXEG</a></div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"λιας Ἀλβίου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"λιας\"><span data-text=\"λιας\">λιας</span></span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀλβίου\">Ἀλβίο[υ]</span></span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: <a href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/UQRFDXEG\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/UQRFDXEG</a></div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"λιας Ἀλβίου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"λιας\"><span data-text=\"λιας\">ΛΙΑΣ</span></span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀλβίου\">ΑΛΒΙΟ[.]</span></span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>Text of Manganaro</span></span>; </li><li><span class=\"1\">1: <span>Manganaro also suggests: [Ἰου(?)]λία Σαλβίο[υ]</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2> translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">  </p><p>  </p></div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Manganaro notes that Albios is attested at Syracuse in IG XIV.70. Whether the text should be understood as relating to the original tomb is unclear. A second text is inscribed on one of the other walls (ISic003034)</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 42.0873.2 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a></li><li> Manganaro 1992 487-492 no.VI figs. 28-29 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001830\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001830</a></li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"><p>Letters of Hellenistic form: broken bar alpha</p> Line 1  130  Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
